[[File:Zeißberg, Heinrich von (1839-1899)2.jpg|thumb|<center>Heinrich von Zeissberg]] '''Heinrich Ritter von Zeissberg''' (8 July 1839, in [[Vienna]] &ndash; 27 May 1899) was an [[Austria]]n [[historian]].
He studied history at the [[university of Vienna]], receiving his PhD in 1862. In 1865 became a professor of history at the [[university of Lemberg]], and in 1871 relocated as a professor to [[University of Innsbruck|Innsbruck]]. In 1872 he was appointed professor at the university of Vienna, and here he was a tutor of history to the [[Crown Prince Rudolf of Austria|crown prince Rudolph]]. In 1892 he was named director of the Vienna institute for historical research, and in 1896 director of the imperial court library at Vienna. He resigned his professorial chair at Vienna in 1897.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=1NVRfl4gCw0C&pg=PA666&lpg=PA666&dq=%22Zeissberg,+Heinrich%22+1839+Lemberg&source=bl&ots=JjwIUwS7Nc&sig=ZlP3lZvgzRtaMNm3pfRfbHmAKA8&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj50di7mZHRAhVF7oMKHUt0BhU4ChDoAQghMAQ#v=onepage&q=%22Zeissberg%2C%20Heinrich%22%201839%20Lemberg&f=false Thibaut - Zycha / edited by Walther Killy] Dictionary of German Biography</ref>
Zeissberg's writings deal mainly with the history of Austria and of [[Poland]], such as: * ''Arno, erster Erzbischof van Salzburg'' (Vienna, 1863) &ndash; [[Arno of Salzburg|Arno]], the first [[Archbishop of Salzburg]]. * ''Miseco I. (Mieczysław) der erste christliche beherrscher der Polen'' (1867) &ndash; [[Mieszko I of Poland|Mieszko I]], the first Christian ruler of Poland. * ''Die Kriege Kaiser Heinrichs II. mit Herzog Boleslaw I. von Polen'' (Vienna, 1868) &ndash; The wars of [[Henry II, Holy Roman Emperor|Emperor Henry II]] with Duke [[Boleslaw I of Poland]]. * ''Die polnische Geschichtsschreibung des Mittelalters'' (Leipzig, 1873) &ndash; Polish [[historiography]] of the Middle Ages. * ''Rudolf von Habsburg und der österreichische Staatsgedanke'' (Vienna, 1882) &ndash; [[Rudolf of Habsburg]] and the Austrian national idea. * ''Über das Rechtsverfahren Rudolfs von Habsburg gegen Ottokar von Böhmen'' (Vienna, 1887) &ndash; On the litigation of Rudolf von Habsburg against [[Ottokar II of Bohemia|Ottokar of Bohemia]]. * ''Der österreichische Erbfolgestreit nach dem Tode des Königs Ladislaus Posthumus, 1457-58'' (Vienna, 1879) &ndash; The Austrian succession dispute after the death of King [[Ladislaus the Posthumous]]. [[File:Gruppendenkmal Theodor von Sickel, Alfons Huber, Engelbert Mühlbacher, Heinrich von Zeißberg.jpg|right|thumb|Group monument; [[Theodor von Sickel]], [[Alfons Huber]], [[Engelbert Mühlbacher]] and '''Heinrich Ritter von Zeissberg''' at the Arkadenhof of Vienna University]] Dealing with more recent times he wrote: * ''Zur deutschen Kaiserpolitik Oesterreichs: ein Beitrag zur Geschichte des Revolutionsjahres 1795'' (Vienna, 1899) &ndash; German imperial policy regarding Austria; a contribution to the history of the revolutionary year 1795. * ''Zwei Jahre belgischer Geschichte 1791-92'' (Vienna, 1891) &ndash; Two years of Belgian history, 1791-92. * ''Belgien unter der Generalstatthalterschaft Erzherzog Karls 1793-94'' (Vienna, 1893-94) &ndash; Belgium under the General Staff of [[Archduke Karl]], 1793-94. * ''Erzherzog Karl von Oesterreich. Lebensbild'' (Vienna, 1895) &ndash; [[Archduke Charles of Austria]], biography. *''Franz Josef I.'' (Vienna, 1888) &ndash; On [[Franz Josef I]]. He edited three volumes of the ''Quellen zur Geschichte der Deutschen Kaiserpolitik Oesterreichs während der französischen Revolutionskriege 1790-1801'' (Vienna, 1882-1885, 1890).<ref>[https://de.wikisource.org/wiki/Heinrich_Ritter_von_Zei%C3%9Fberg Heinrich Ritter von Zeißberg] de.Wikisource] (bibliography)</ref> He was the author of 61 biographies in the ''[[Allgemeine Deutsche Biographie]]''.<ref>[https://de.wikisource.org/wiki/Kategorie:ADB:Autor:Heinrich_Ritter_von_Zei%C3%9Fberg Kategorie:ADB:Autor:Heinrich Ritter von Zeißberg] at [[Allgemeine Deutsche Biographie]]</ref>
