{{infobox person/Wikidata|fetchwikidata=ALL|dateformat=mdy|onlysourced=yes|list=hlist}}
'''Johann Georg Lairitz''' (July 15, 1647 – April 4, 1716) was a German theologian, was born July 15, 1641, at [[Hof, Bavaria|Hof]], in [[Bavaria]]. In 1667 he entered the [[University of Jena|university at Jena]]; in 1677 he was graduated [[Master of Arts|M.A.]], and became in 1673 professor of Church and profane history at the gymnasium of [[Bayreuth|Baireuth]]; in 1675, librarian and instructor of the [[margrave]]s Erdmann Philipp and [[Georg Albrecht, Margrave of Brandenburg-Bayreuth-Kulmbach|Georg Albrecht]]; in 1685, deacon of the court Church; in 1688, superintendent at Neustadt. In 1697 he accepted the call of the [[William Ernest, Duke of Saxe-Weimar|duke Wilhelm Ernst of Weimar]], and he then became superintendent in general, counselor of the consistory, first preacher of the Petri-Paul Church, and director of the gymnasium. He died April 4, 1716.

He left numerous productions, e.g. ''Diss. de simplici et composito'' (Jenae, 1668, 4to): — ''Auszug der Kirchengeschichte des Neuen Testans.'' (Baireuth und Niremb. 1678, 12mo): ''— Synopsis historiae ecclesiasticae Novi Testam.'' (ibid. 1678, 12mo): — ''Der romische Papst-Thron, d. i. gründliche und ausführliche Beschreibung des papstlichen Ehrund Macht-und Wachsthums'' (ibid, 1685, 4to).

